Draw two big circular balls to make out the eyes across the central horizontal line. These will form the eye sockets. The top of this circle is where the eyebrow is and at the bottom is where the cheekbone sits. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/6/6f/Draw-a-Face-Step-5Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Draw-a-Face-Step-5Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/6/6f/Draw-a-Face-Step-5Bullet1.jpg/v4-760px-Draw-a-Face-Step-5Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Draw the eyebrows along the top. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/c/ca/Draw-a-Face-Step-5Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Draw-a-Face-Step-5Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/c/ca/Draw-a-Face-Step-5Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Draw-a-Face-Step-5Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

You then need to work on the shape of the eyes. Eyes are almond shaped, so bear this in mind as you sketch them (eyes come in every size and shape, so feel it out). As a rule of thumb, the distance between the two eyes is the width of another eye. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/7/72/Draw-a-Face-Step-5Bullet3.jpg/v4-460px-Draw-a-Face-Step-5Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/7/72/Draw-a-Face-Step-5Bullet3.jpg/v4-760px-Draw-a-Face-Step-5Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Inside the iris, the color inside the center of the eye, draw the pupil, which is the darkest bit of the eye. Fill most of it in black and leave a little white. With your pencil flat, use a bit of shading for the base. Shade variant from medium and light in the iris, using tightly spaced short lines from the edge of the pupil to the white of the eye. Draw lighter in some areas to give it a nice effect. Draw eyebrows above. Now rub out the guidelines below the eye. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/e/e1/Draw-a-Face-Step-5Bullet4.jpg/v4-460px-Draw-a-Face-Step-5Bullet4.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/e/e1/Draw-a-Face-Step-5Bullet4.jpg/v4-760px-Draw-a-Face-Step-5Bullet4.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Next, draw the top of the eyelid over the top of the almond. The base of the eyelid comes down over the top of the iris and covers the top of it slightly. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/9/90/Draw-a-Face-Step-5Bullet5.jpg/v4-460px-Draw-a-Face-Step-5Bullet5.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/9/90/Draw-a-Face-Step-5Bullet5.jpg/v4-760px-Draw-a-Face-Step-5Bullet5.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}
